<title>Multiple Choice</title>
<exercise id="fs-idm178755408">
<problem id="fs-idm163329248">
<para id="fs-idm183832656"><link class="lo-reference" document="m67886"/>Which of the following is true of a maturity date?</para>
<list id="fs-idm199474592" list-type="enumerated" number-style="upper-alpha">
<item>It must be calculated in days, not in months or years.</item>
<item>It is the date when principal and interest on a note are to be repaid to the lender.</item>
<item>It is the date of establishment of note terms between a lender and customer.</item>
<item>It is not a characteristic of a note receivable.</item>
</list>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idm200974160">
<para id="fs-idm218645296">B</para>
