<section id="fs-idm223475408" class="thought-provokers">
<title>Thought Provokers</title>
<exercise id="fs-idm185723680">
<problem id="fs-idm202550352">
<para id="fs-idm201190816"><link class="lo-reference" document="m67886"/>When a customer is delinquent on paying a notes receivable, your company has the option to continue to attempt collection or sell the debt to a collection agency. Research the benefits and challenges with each of these options and in a short essay, answer the following questions.</para>
<list id="fs-idm225764240" list-type="enumerated" number-style="upper-alpha">
<item>What are the benefits and challenges of continuing to attempt collection yourself?</item>
<item>What are the benefits and challenges of selling debt to a collection agency?</item>
<item>If you had a dishonored notes receivable, which option would you select and why?</item>
<item>Would you weight certain benefits or challenges differently when making your selection? How?</item>
</list>
</problem>
</exercise>
</section>
